title: Freddie Hubbard Interview 1995

http_headers.User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/72.0.3626.110 Safari/537.36

description: Really great interview with Freddie from November 4, 1995.  Freddie talks about his days in the Bronx, Kenny Dorham's influence and friendship, Blue Note records' Alfred Lion and Francis Wolff, the Montgomery brothers, composing technique, the difference between NY and LA, and other subjects.
